# {name}

Minimal firmware for **{cpp_define}** (board **{name}** target), generated by the
ViewAlyzer `scaffold` tool. It blinks the onboard LED (GPIO{led_port} pin {led_pin}) with
raw HAL_GPIO — portable, no vendor BSP.

## Build

```sh
cmake --preset Debug
cmake --build --preset Debug
# -> build/Debug/{name}.elf  (ELF 32-bit ARM)
```

Requires `arm-none-eabi-gcc`, `cmake` and `ninja` on `PATH`.

## Layout

- `Core/Src/main.c` — `HAL_Init` → `SystemClock_Config` (MSI) → LED init → blink loop.
- `Core/Src/{family_l}xx_it.c` — Cortex-M fault handlers + `SysTick_Handler` (HAL timebase).
- `startup_{cmsis_device}.s`, `Core/Src/system_{family_l}xx.c` — vendored CMSIS startup/init.
- `{cpp_define}_FLASH.ld` — linker script (memory map from the part's datasheet).
- `Drivers/` — vendored HAL + CMSIS subset (`--gc-sections` strips the unused HAL).

Edit `SystemClock_Config` in `main.c` to retarget the clock frequency.
